data.OTHER_INFORMATION: UNITED KINGDOM: Scotland: Angus (VC 90): Carnoustie, 250m NE of Barry Budden Army firing range. Behind retaining sea wall and sprawling out onto the foreshore of the sandy beach by the children's playpark. 1 m. NO562 341. Perennial plant with extensive rhizomes, glaucous grey foliage and saggitate stipules. Petals shocking pink, often with paler (near-white) wings and keel. Forming extensive patches (100m x 5m continuous stretch. Many flowers and mature fruits at same time - an excellent season! Kenicer, Greg J; Towll, Andrew s.n. 13 Jul 2009.
